                  <p> (1) The day of the month recorded in the date is wrong: the scribe wrote 10,
                     it should be 11, as shown by the co-occurence on that day of all the other
                     calendrical elements. (2) Possibly, Veṅkiṭācam was a student of the text who
                     copied it into this manuscript.</p>
